@{_Section "História das Versões"}

v1.0     (May 31, 2000)@{par}
@{_bullet2}First Public Release!@{LIndent 2}


v1.1     (June 21, 2000)@{par}
@{_bullet2}Demo expiry date was being incorrectly calculated.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Date & Time conduit sync completed [registered users only]@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Re-wrote routines that took into account 'virgin' (ID=0) Palms.  Things should be much better now with changing user names and ids on Palms.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}datebook.conduit did not always return a text error to log file.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}datebook.conduit would try to open 'datbookdb' instead of 'datebookdb' on restoring files (Amiga->Handheld).@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}todo.conduit did not always return text error to log file.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Cleaned up some code in memo and address conduits.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}In order to handle username changes without userid changes on handheld devices, the userid is now appended to directories that are created for database storage.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}First new user to Spitfire would not be seen until a restart.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}users.dat file updated before clients are notified of new user addition.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Changed all desktop apps to support new user path directory name format.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}HSM was doubling usernames in listviews when multiple users present.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}The file pocketchess.prc was being distributed with the Spitfire² archive. It has been removed.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Under OS 3.1 the icon images for DAM are now all the same height.@{LIndent 2}


v1.2     (July 8, 2000)@{par}
@{_bullet2}If a required library was not found by HSM then it would crash on exit.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Added editing of users to HSM.  Deletion of user currently completed.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}If items in date, address, to do, and memos were deleted but not archived on the handheld side then the changes were not properly being reflected on the Amiga side.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Find in the Address desktop app was not working correctly.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}SpitfireHSM would crash if application was terminated with open windows.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Now all windows should be properly disposed of to ward off the Guru!@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Fixed crashing of HSM when in demo mode.@{LIndent 2}


v1.3     (November 8, 2000)@{par}
@{_bullet2}Datebook app entries must now have a valid description when created. Seems that the PalmOS does not like a NULL field for descriptions and will crash if one is found (bug in PalmOS?).@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Activated MUI ARexx port for HSM.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Any entries in Datebook, ToDo, and Memo with NULL description fields will be automatically deleted.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}It appears that the Palm Datebook allows the erasing of event description but does not delete the event.  This places an "invisible" entry in the Palm Datebook and is no problem until you do a "find" on your Palm. Once this record is accessed your Palm will crash.  Spitfire will now search for these records and mark them for deletion at subsequent HotSyncs.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Ability to show/hide image texts via settings for DAM added.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}If there were no records on the Amiga and Palm, and then new records were created on the Palm, they would not be copied over onto the Amiga side. This affected the Address, Datebook, ToDo, and Memo applications.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}All desktop apps now save data to a standard .pdb file.  Existing .dat files are still recognized, but will be converted and deleted the first time the desktop/conduit is loaded.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Fixed several grammer and spelling mistakes in English catalogs.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Fixed crashing of HSM when exiting, if the Edit user window was ever accessed during the use of HSM.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}spitfireAPI.library no longer trips up with usernames having periods i.e. Michael W. Smith)@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}A User Guide available in PDF format! (Thanks to Duncan Turner for writing the user guide)@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Fixed problem of identifing ID number extensions from folder names if the users.dat file was deleted.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Changed demo expiry date.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}All the conduits would start scanning their repective database at index 1 instead of 0.  This would result in some data not appearing to be synced.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Failed memory allocations were going unchecked in spitfireAPI.library.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Change ERRORID_OPENDAT text for conduit locale.@{LIndent 2}


v1.4     (February 7, 2001)@{par}
@{_bullet2}Added "Desktop..." button to HSM main window.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Datebook app can now create events that have the same and end times.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Fixed bug in which Datebook app would create 2 new events for every one a user created.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Address CSV import can now handle MS-DOS files (cr-lf).@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Memo Pad import would truncate files at 4000 bytes instead of 4k.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Internal changes to HSM to help increase its stability.  Also increase of stack space for conduits and HSM throttle process.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Updated Installation script, adding ability to update ilbm/picture datatype files available from Aminet (suggested by Roger Fullans)@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Added some checks to system.conduit in case it fails to allocate required memory.  This conduit can still crash at times, and always from the MUI interface it opens.  Still trying to find a bullet-proof fix...@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Modified sync routines in conduits.  Hopefully this should properly sync data now.@{LIndent 2}


v1.5     (February 24, 2001)@{par}
@{_bullet2}Bad news. I lost the source code to the address.desktop application!  The good news is that I did have a back up, unfortunately it is version 1.2.  I hope that I fixed everything to get it back to the current version...@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Reworked the HotSync feedback window.  It now shows the user, status of the HotSync, and details from the specific conduit so...@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Install.conduit and system.conduit now do not open their own MUI gui. As a result, new functionality has been added to the HSM server port.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}ASCII files imported into Memo Pad that are larger than 4k are now broken into several memos.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Changing the prefs data directory will now cause the HSM to scan and update for users, and sends broadcast message to clients.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Did some more tweaking of the sync routines in all conduits.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Increased stack of throttle process to 20000@{LIndent 2}


v1.6     (June 4, 2001)@{par}
@{_bullet2}Fixed bug in categories not being properly synchronized between the Palm and Amiga.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}vectorser.device should now be recognized by HSM.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Implemented ability for user to skip certain files on backups via a new desktop application called "System Backup" (system.desktop).@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Install desktop application can now load in any datatype supported text format and convert it into a Palm DOC format. Requires DocDatatypes by Amarpreet Singh Munde. (email: docdatatypes@yahoo.com OR http://go.to/docdatatypes).  Thanks A.S.Munde for the aide in programming this ability.  Now go register and support his excellent work if you need this functionality!@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet2}Re-compiled the New8N1.device source codes for ignoring DSR.  This is to be used with Visor users and the Amiga's internal serial port.  This is not the best serial.device replacement, thus it may not work on your system to the "hackish" style of the code.@{LIndent 2}

@endnode



@node "Future" "Futuro"
@next "Main"
@prev "History"


@{_Section "Futuro"}
Envie-me as suas sugestões para novas funções do Spitfire²!

Novas características planeadas:

@{_bullet}Importar/Exportar elementos do To Do no formato CSV.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet}Um tipo de letra Spitfire.font que inclua todos os glifos suportados pelo PalmOS.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet}Documentação mais pormenorizada (embore eu não aprecie muito estar a escrever documentação...)@{LIndent 2}


Características sugeridas por utilizadores:

@{_bullet}"Conduit" para email - Gostava de criar um "conduit" deste género, mas o meu PalmPilot não tem programas de email, pelo que me é impossível programá-lo :-(@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet}Porta ARexx.@{LIndent 2}

@endnode



